Fans and loyal consumers of Heineken in and around Lagos are set for a memorable UEFA Champions League final experience as the brand is set to light up the Centre of Excellence with its magic. Though tomorrow’s final clash between Liverpool and Real Madrid is holding thousands of miles away at the Stade de France, Heineken will be relieving the eclectic atmosphere in Paris at Cubana in the heart of Ikeja. This is the third clash between these two giants of world football in the UCL final. Aside from the guaranteed unique match viewing experience on giant screens in a first-class lounge, Heineken has promised instant giveaways to fans and loyal customers alike. In its usual style of mixing football action with A-class entertainment, there would be DJs on the ground led by DJ CrowdKontroller. Senior Brand Manager, Heineken, Chinwe Greg-Egu, described this season’s Champions League as a worthy journey deserving of a classic final. She said: “Though it has been a hectic run, we are set for an epic final and thanks to Heineken, the fans have an extra reason to look forward to Saturday as we will be providing everything that would make the night an unforgettable one.”